03/05/2009
NICOSIA, Cyprus -- A court in Nicosia adjourned on Thursday (April 30th) until June 4th in the trial against four people facing charges over an August 2005 Cypriot Helios Airways airplane crash that killed all 121 people onboard. The accused include two executive officers, the chief pilot trainer and operations manager of the Cypriot Helios Airways. The four face multiple manslaughter and death-through-negligence charges. Under the Cyprus's penal code, manslaughter is punishable by life sentences. (Cyprus Mail, Reuters, CNA- 01/05/09)
